    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Soft red ocher that is a natural mixture of hydrated silicate clays colored with red iron oxide. Since at least the 17th century, it has been used as a foundation for gold leaf and as a red earth pigment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
